Niger State chapter of the Nigeria Union of Teachers NUT, has
inaugurated its permanent secretariat and ultra-modern school. The state NUT chairman, Comrade Ibrahim Umar, said the construction of
the Secretariat and the School started ten years ago, and were built
through direct labour with 45 percent share of monthly dues collected
by the state chapter. Comrade Umar further stated that the wing has valuable investments
that are beneficial to its members and the state in general. He listed some of the investments as, building of affordable estate
for members, shopping plaza, Endwell micro finance Bank LTD, and other
things that would bring about multiplier effect for members of the
union. Meanwhile, Niger state Governor, Abubakar Sani Bello, has said that
his government is making deliberate efforts to formulate a policy to
empower teachers as a priority and panacea for quality education. He said at the occasion, that qualitative education for students
cannot be achieved without first standardizing the quality of those
who impact knowledge in students at all levels of the educational
system. The Governor, who was represented by the State Commissioner of
Education, Hajiya Hannatu Jibrin Salihu, noted that the administration
accords high premium to the teaching profession in the state. Hajiya Hannatu explained that the overall target for education is to
ensure the creation of a functional and sustainable system that
supports the development of character and learning in youths for the
socio- economic development, reiterating that teachers were the most
critical stakeholders in the achievement of this goal.